A week has passed since the siege, and at this time when people in Wuhan and Hubei are turning Pale, we want to have a good look at them. Today we have selected several reader contributions that revolve around Wuhan and Huanggang in Hubei Province, telling of their days in the Vortex and Storm Center. Some of them live in cities, some in villages and small towns. Different circumstances give them different feelings and experiences. These records remind us that the people of the Han River Plain, where Tam Giang converges, are not strangers to us, not outliers to be guarded, but, at this moment, like you and me, wHO's anxious and wants to get on with their lives.

You must live well in Hubei

Wuhan

January 26,2020

Before everything

By Tong Yibo

Last December just arrived, my first half year in Wuhan University insouciantly entered the countdown. At the time, the city, which was still thriving, was mired in a deep, cold, damp climate, and everyone was praying for a beautiful, empty future as they struggled with their end of the year jobs.

At that time, the center of public opinion, but also lively to stay in the Forbidden City that the mysterious mercedes-benz woman. As usual, people on the Internet are opening their minds to add entertainment.

At the beginning of the New Year, everything is still in good order. A few days ago, the deafening New Year's eve celebration on Chuhehan street was still floating around my ears hazily. Wearing a mask for us is still just a casual joke, when the class behind several girls in serious discussion mask must buy black, face small easy to take pictures.

On January 5th, rumors of the cause of SARS were ruled out, and the disease remained ethereal in its veil. That day I asked in the supermarket downstairs of the dormitory if there were any masks for sale. The aunt at the cash register asked me why so many students have come to buy masks in the past few days. I was thinking of answering, "You haven't heard, " said the woman at the other counter. "Some people in Kong Hon have pneumonia and don't know why. " "Huh? What are we GONNA do? I haven't even bought a mask yet, is it serious? " "No, no, no, just a few people are sick. It doesn't seem to be contagious, I heard. "

After a few more uneventful days, on January 9, we finished all our exams and began to make preparations for our return home. It was on that day that the mysterious disease was called a "COVID-19. " . At first sight, I had peace of mind, to their own shallow experience, after the name, control and elimination should not be too far away. Home side with a group of people are about to return gradually lively up, the atmosphere of the New Year slowly weaving. The school never released information about pneumonia, and the mask slowly faded out of our sight. I Look Online, the disease has not been many people mentioned, like a very long time ago, everything seems to be moving towards a good round smooth.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The movie "Southern Station Party" , the urban flavor of Hubei Small Town

On January 11, the day before I left Wuhan, I put off going out with my friends and ran to Moshan, east lake, alone, like a pretentious escape. Far from the Hustle and bustle of the countryside, I head to the East L. Museum of art and to the green streets of East L. , Florida. Along the way I met a few people, some to see the exhibition, some in the walk, everyone is quietly bathed in their own comfortable life. As for the disaster that came soon after, it still seemed like a distant dream.

At that time, the temperature was nearly zero, I was in the desolate mountain road against the cold wind drift. When I got tired, I sat down on a rotten wooden bench by the side of the road and was surprised to find a small stone Buddha lying alone in the grass beside me. I did not know where it came from. Wuhan's winter sunset very early, at four o'clock in the afternoon, the sun has already had the desire language also to rest the meaning of return. I got up to leave, casting my last glance over the empty hills around me. When is the next time you think of nature's reticent nature, which has endured us for most of the past eleven million odd years, with the exception of a rare case of anger?

Think of this, in the mind involuntarily reappear that is near at hand disease, hurriedly laugh at oneself redundant worry. The little stone Buddha on the ground was looking at me quietly, his nearly worn-out eyes flashing nimbly. It didn't say anything. It seemed to say everything.

January 27,2020

Face the virus, face yourself

By Wu Dong

Today is January 27,2020, the third day of the first lunar month.

I'm in my room, in my home, in a suburb of Wuhan, Hubei Province, in the countryside. The word "Wuhan" should be famous all over the world now.

On New Year's Eve, I always felt a little sick, chest tightness, even a little dizzy. It was hard for me not to panic, it was hard not to think in that way, if it was a coronavirus infection, what would I do, crowded in a noisy hospital, pneumonia step by step, but also will infect the family, even thought if I die what to do, body cold, then I found I was so afraid of death, afraid of all this. That day I went to our town hospital, the town hospital is not a lot of people, the hospital gave me a temperature check, a stethoscope to listen to the lungs, everything is OK, give me some cold medicine. I went to bed early that night after the New Year's Eve dinner. I didn't watch any Spring Festival gala or Party. I was glad to wake up the next day feeling good and not feeling sick.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, as in previous years, we all went to visit graves in the mountains. In the countryside, the epidemic didn't stop this, but unlike in previous years, most people wore masks. In the countryside you can hardly ask everyone to stay at home. For them, the New Year is the most important time of the year. They visit each other to play Mahjong and chat. The New Year is also the most popular time of the year in the village. On the afternoon of the first day came the news that Wuhan City will be closed to motor vehicles. These days there are too many kinds of news about the epidemic. They keep coming at us. Most of them are bad. On the second day of the Lunar New Year, every village around Wuhan was told to close the road leading into the village, and so was our village.

I want to talk about the people I know who are really suffering from the new pneumonia. My father told me that a relative's uncle had died of pneumonia. He was in his fifties. The other day, at the Golden Pool Hospital, I didn't know if he was on the official death list. And there was a confirmed infection in the town next to ours, and then the whole village was sealed off. A classmate of mine said one of his dad's coworkers had the virus, too. My Aunt said that a man in their old neighborhood got sick, and then he got it from the doctors at the community clinic. Of all the cases of viral infection I've heard about, there's probably about 10 of them around me, and I can feel that the virus might be around me, threatening me and my family.

The first day of the first day I went to a grandma's house, when I was a child and grandma lived for a period of time, we have a good relationship. The other day I told her to take care of herself. My grandmother is a very kind old woman who has been in the village for most of her life. She said that these are things that God has to collect people from. What is a virus? Whoever the Lord of death wants will go away. It can't be stopped, or do you want to live your life. Grandma is 77 years old this year. China was still at war when she was born. It's hard for you to tell her what science has taught us. I don't want to contradict what grandma taught me, it's important to live your life.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan in the 1990s in the movie "Arrow through the heart"

These days I also look at the mobile phone less, more to see home. Today, there is no rain in Wuhan, the Sun came out for a while and went back, I stood at my window, looking out the window of the home field, there is a very familiar feeling, but it seems and I remember when the field is not the same. The village behind Feng village is very quiet, unlike the New Year village, there are a few birds hanging in the winter bare branches, issued a pleasant voice.

Huanggang

January 28,2020

Diary of a Huanggang Seal

By Ma Yi

Like yesterday, I didn't wake up until nine o'clock in the morning. Some sunshine came through the Glass Window. The weather was fine and steady at last.

It's day four of the town's total lockdown. After the first three days of depression, the front of my house on the county road than yesterday's motor vehicles up significantly, every few minutes to see a car. But there was still no one on the road, only two or three people standing in front of their own door in the open stretch, or standing in a daze.

Because I'm in the middle of a new outbreak of pneumonia, there's a lot of indecipherable information coming from all over my phone. Since the day before yesterday I have deliberately cut down on the number of times I swipe my phone, and I can feel that even rumors that are obviously false are adding to my own panic.

After breakfast, I picked up my mobile phone and saw the middle school students who had not moved for a long time had already burst into flames. A student working as a doctor in the county hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine sent out a large number of photos and text of the real situation on the spot, for emergency assistance. After the first three days of self-isolation, I sat on the Second Floor Sofa in my home and watched TV every day. Although the number of infected people kept rising, it didn't seem to be a real threat to myself, in the mind actually produced a kind of environment is still relatively safe illusion.

For the average person, the biggest concern is, of course, whether there are cases of infection around them. I have also been watching the situation in Hubei Province and Huanggang these days. According to official figures, there were more than 150 cases in Huanggang and three in my county. For a county with a population of more than one million, three cases is a number that can be almost completely ignored, at least psychologically. But the student, who is fighting a new form of pneumonia, told me that the isolation ward on the third floor of his hospital was fully occupied, ready to open the fourth floor today. If anyone had told me the news, I would have said it was a rumor, but the middle school classmate was a doctor at the hospital, and sourcing circumstances was not in doubt.

According to the students, our county's main position in the fight against new pneumonia in the county people's Hospital, and his hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine was not listed as a designated hospital until yesterday. Since even the most non-major TCM hospitals are full of three-story isolation wards, the confirmed and suspected cases in the People's hospital are really an unimaginable mystery.

The students sent me a bunch of screenshots of various medical staff and their circle of friends, the basic idea being that there is a severe lack of medical equipment in Florida. There are at least a few examples of what really happens to doctors at their hospitals:

Many medical staff who have been working day and night for many days can not leave work, and those who want to take over can not take over, because there is no protective gear.

Multiple paramedics slept only five or six hours over three days and two nights.

A doctor collapsed in the stairwell, but luckily he was found in time.

Everyone's been wearing diapers for days.

Corresponding to the difficult circumstances of front-line doctors, this morning, after staying at home for three days, I looked at the fine weather outside and actually felt a little bit relieved of pressure. Although it is Fengcheng, Fengcun, but to this day, I am in the streets are not used usually nothing to shout out loud speakers to tell everyone to stay at home, the first three days of not leaving the house, relying on full awareness. Students in neighboring towns said that to this day, there are still people in the villages who hang out in small groups or walk around without masks. And no one seems to be stopping it.

I'm in the county seat of Huanggang. Because the outbreak began in Wuhan, the city was at first the absolute center of Media Coverage and aid. With the progress of the epidemic, the cities around Wuhan have also received some attention. Huanggang is the second most populous city in the province, after Wuhan, and is just an hour or so away from the centre of Wuhan. Wuhan has seen rapid economic growth in recent years, so it has been the first choice for many Huanggang people to work outside the city. In my family, at least half of my relatives work or live in Wuhan. That is why Huanggang has consistently ranked second in terms of the number of people infected, according to official figures. And My county, which is the most populous county in Huanggang, has a population of over a million. In various media channels, we can see that major hospitals in many provinces and cities are calling for assistance in medical care equipment. It is conceivable that from the gaps in provincial and municipal hospitals to the People's hospitals in counties, to my classmates yesterday was listed in the Designated Hospital Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine, the current gap in medical care has how huge.

Since I was officially closed on the first day of the Lunar New Year, I began to update my diary on my personal account to record what I had seen and thought during this difficult time. And today after seeing the information sent by my classmates, I also sorted out the relevant information in time and pushed it out through my wechat public account, which only has 300 followers. I know it's not much, but it's better to do it than not to do it.

January 28,2010

The story of the city's closure

By toussie

On the morning of the 23rd, I received a text message from the Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters.

At this time also has not been discharged, but also to carry out the second round of coronal bacteria test paper, as well as various types of viral anti-inflammatory drug infusion. Hands have been inserted with a needle, isolation ward, the doctor ordered after the cold, no one around.

The only thing that's left is the sound of us talking every two hours.

For three days, without a definitive test result, all that fear and worry proved to be a rare sign of human heat.

All this time, the judgment of human dogmatism, in my eyes, somewhat empty. For most people, there is no such thing as unthinking good, and there is no such thing as pure evil. There have been many predicaments in human nature since ancient times. Otherwise, where would literature and art go? Thus human nature is never a judgment, but a growth to be expected.

He and I, we've come a long way together. Those from the outside of the wind and rain, not to destroy us, but let us embrace more closely. Each time in the face of hardship and choice, there is always a person from beginning to end never let go of each other's hand. So two hedgehogs run away from the grief, finally found in each other can make their own complete things, and finally learned how to embrace each other. The significance of this moment, in fact, the two hedgehogs, are made of sponge, differences in the past, the concept of the debate, and at this time soft, too insignificant.

It's a delicate feeling, and I've only just learned it, but at this age, there's a magical attraction to sharing, as if it gives meaning to a shallow life. There is nothing more to look forward to in our already poor lives.

Fortunately, three days later, also safe discharge from the hospital, my heart is also temporarily stable some. Just the current situation in Wuhan, in which I, anxiety for a while there is no place to put.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan in the movie Mystery

The disaster was so unexpected that we had to walk through the crowded Hankou Station without any protection, and on the back foot there was an emergency alert.

The first case is located in the south China Seafood Market, less than a few kilometers from the giant platform of Foshan, Hankou, with thousands of people passing through every day. It is one of the largest floating population gathering places in Wuhan, and is a new coronavirus with air media, it's a human parasite that breathes, which makes resistance somewhat Pale. Therefore, during the Spring Festival travel period, people from the Han Dynasty caused infection in other provinces, the probability of infection is so large, there is no reason. Until the city before the seafood market is still normal operation, from the first case of infection to the city, before and after the time has been nearly a month. The incubation period is 14 days, which means there have been at least two rounds of cloaking since the end of December, which was only the first outbreak before the city was shut down. The number of infected people has risen by hundreds these days. The second round is not far away. However, the next round of resistance in Wuhan will be the third and fourth round

Over the past few days, both Weibo and friends have been inspired by Wuhan's establishment of the Little Tangshan fo fo Shen Shan Hospital.

Seventeen years ago in the face of SARS, the epidemic situation could not be controlled, the tense doctor-patient relationship led to the collapse of a large number of medical staff, Peking University Hospital once closed down, under such circumstances Xiaotangshan is completely helpless.

Seventeen years later, we seem to have made very little progress. People are moved by the sounds from all over the country. Wuhan's empty roads, with no pedestrians, no sirens, are "helpless" in all directions.

As for the Vulcan Mountain Hospital, I have all kinds of doubts. When preparing to build the Vulcan Mountain Hospital, only more than 600 patients were reported in Wuhan. There are dozens of third-class hospitals in this city, affiliated hospitals of various universities, and they are known throughout the country as Tongji, Xiehe, the only P4 lab in Asia. If it is true that more than 600, why to build a bed can accommodate thousands of small Tangshan it? It's not that I'm negative or pessimistic, it's that we're always passive in certain things.

You know what? I live three blocks from the river, and even if I can't see it, I know it's still moving east. Even though I can't see him at this moment, I know that his thoughts are stored far away. Though I can't hear the car now, one day it will return to the earth.

Two days ago, ambulance to the next area of the alarm sound, a long ring, since then, the four wild quietly only the wind, rain, heartbeat sound.

Murakami has an article, "love like a midnight whistle, " his description of love is quite unique. At the end he wrote: "The whistle, indeed, is faint, and I love you like the whistle. "

Since the essay, we have received a large number of submissions, writing truthfully about what they saw and heard during the epidemic. It will be a sincere and weighty record, and we will keep it.
